            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-04T08:10:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-04T08:10:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890.00B/1–449: Circular airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Certain American Missions</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d307fn1">Sent to 15 posts at Bangkok, Batavia, Canberra,
                        Colombo, Hanoi, Karachi, Manila, Moscow, Nanking, New Delhi, Paris, Rangoon,
                        Saigon, Singapore, and The Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-04T08:10:00-05:00">January 4, 1949—8:10 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Containment of Communism in Southeast Asia</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Embassy London states that the UK Foreign Office feels that because of political
                    differences it would be impossible to bring Asiatic and western nations together
                    at a conference to discuss the containment of Communism in southeast Asia. The
                    Foreign Office hopes to arrange continuing discussions through diplomatic
                    channels with all countries concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
